[1]
Date: Mon, 27 Oct 2003 10:40:02 -0800
From: Richard I. Frankel <Richard.Frankel@med.va.gov>

_Staphylococcus aureus_ has been recovered from ocean water in Hawaii
and elsewhere. This organism can survive in salt water. I suspect
that MRSA can survive in this environment just as well as
methicillin-susceptible _S. aureus_. This certainly does not prove
that these infections were acquired in the ocean, but I do not think
it is necessary to invoke _V. vulnificus_ unless there are clinical
data to implicate that organism.
--
Richard I. Frankel MD, MPH
Associate Chief of Staff for Education
VA Pacific Islands Health Care System
Honolulu, Hawaii
<Richard.Frankel@med.va.gov>
